-- 2014 world trade picture improves but still below trend - WTO
-- By Tom Miles
-- Mon Apr 14, 2014 06:36AM EDT
-- None



GENEVA, April 14 (Reuters) - The World Trade Organization revised its 2014 forecast for growth in global goods trade slightly upward to 4.7 percent on Monday, but said it did not expect growth to return to the historical trend level of 5.3 percent until 2015.

